        <div class="excerpt">
            The book Computer Networks by Andrew S Tanenbaum mentions the following (paraphrased):


  For a noiseless channel, Nyquist theorem states:
    Maximum data rate = \$2H \space log_{2} V \$ bits/sec
  
...
